node.text:
The second half of goldRush Rally was just as intense as the first, however, in different ways. Less curvy mountain roads. More stretches of long backroads to open it up. 

All teams enjoyed dinner at @chateau_elan . The following day @gigipapasavvass @1016industries unveiled STYCH V2 at our second half start grid at @hondacarlandga 
We then made our way to Memphis for a night of amazing food and music at @bbkingsmemphis . 

@maymaysworld_ shut down NOLA and treated us to an hour long police escort through the city streets. Our participants had a delicious meal at @themillnola including entertainment by a traditional New Orleans style band. Then, off to Houston where we enjoyed an incredible dinner thanks to @sportingclubhtx followed by champagne showers at @concretecowboyhtx . 

On our last day we made our way to @hennesseyperformance for some good old fashion drag racing and Texas BBQ. @glossit raised $5,000 for @taylorlynnfoundation racing his modified TRX @ramtrucks . goldRush Rally awards ceremony took place at @happiesthourdal thanks to @parkupfront . Next stop, @virginhotelsdal where it was tome to rest up and end our nine day adventure at the mist happening club in Dallas, @citizendallas .  Until our next adventure.... #goldbloodedforlife 📹 @jnitek @bt.photo

node.text:
The first half of goldRush Rally took us from New York City, Washington D.C., White Sulphur Springs, Asheville, and ended outside of Atlanta at @chateau_elan . Our participants enjoyed some incredible mountain roads, track time at @atlantamotorsportspark ,  delicious dinners at places like @wolfgangssteakhouse , and a show stopping unveiling by @swae.us of their 24k gold Huracan at @cccmanhattan .  Enjoy the recap by @jnitek @bt.photo .

node.text:
2020 has been a challenge, but that didn't stop goldRush Rally from putting together one of the most epic routes this country has ever seen. For our participants, relive memories that you'll never forget. For the rest of you, well, ponder over what you missed, and know that the goldRush Rally 2021 Tour is a MUST GO.  Let us know when you're ready. We have a spot reserved for you. 

GR2020 - Title Sponsor - @1stphorm 

#goldrushrally #GR2020

node.title: Goldrush Rally 2020 The Road Less Traveled

node.text:
Today we are taking you back to GRX, our ten-year anniversary in 2018. On gRX, we started in Boston and ended in Las Vegas. This was a journey! We visited the Barrett Jackson auctions at Mohegan Sun on our way to New York City. We then headed to Nemacolin Resort right outside of Pennsylvania where we had one unforgettable night! Now it was time to hit the track at M1 Motorsports followed by an unforgettable police escort into Detroit thanks to Platinum Motorsports. St. Louis was our next city, but we first took to the track at Indianapolis Motor Speedway, a bucket list experience for sure! The next morning, we enjoyed a tour of 1st Phorm headquarters before we made our way to Memphis for some BBQ and Blues. We turned up the heat in Dallas with VIP treatment at Concrete Cowboy Dallas and flew by a few UFOs as we headed to Albuquerque. Two more cities left including Scottsdale. gR Exotic car drag races at Albuquerque Dragway went down, followed by an incredible rive through the mountains before we touched down in Las Vegas at Carroll Shelby Museum.  Catch the full flick on our YouTube Channel!
⠀
⠀
Title Sponsor: @1stPhorm

node.text:
On GRS7EVEN in 2015, we started at the Pacific Ocean in San Diego and ended at the Atlantic Ocean in Miami. This was the first year our title sponsor @1stphorm joined us and they have been with us ever since! Thank you for your support Pham! In San Diego, we had breakfast on a battleship then enjoyed being the featured marque at HRE Open house. Our next city was Las Vegas where we partied the night away! With a little extra time to sleep in, we headed to Sedona, Arizona where Bugatti treated us to an unforgettable dining experience at Enchantment Resort. The next city, Santa Fe, our teams would jump on a plane and fly to Austin, Texas However, a few of the teams went the extra "miles" and drove instead! We spent two days in Austin with track time at Circuit of the Americas and our first Concrete Cowboy experience! Now the next day we went to New Orleans and this day went down in the books as far as police escorts go! We had a 23-mile police escort into the French Quarter thanks to one of our teams that year! We flew through the Panhandle and stayed in Jacksonville before reaching our final city, Miami. Catch all of the GRS7EVEN Episodes on our YouTube Channel!
⠀
